# Template href vs path: Baseurl Footgun

**Common footgun**: Using `path` or `_path` (site-relative, no baseurl) instead of `href` (includes baseurl) for link URLs. This breaks GitHub Pages project sites where the site lives under a subpath (e.g. `/lbliii/`).

**Works with**: `implementation/add-directive`, `implementation/add-filter`

---

## Rule of Thumb

| Use case | Prefer | Avoid |
|----------|--------|-------|
| `href` attributes, `<a href="...">` | `href` | `path`, `_path` |
| Pagination base URLs | `href` | `path`, `_path` |
| Any URL used in links | `href` | `path`, `_path` |
| Current-page checks | `_path` | `href` |
| Cache keys, deduplication | `_path` | `href` |

---

## Correct

```html
{# Link URLs - always include baseurl #}
<a href="{{ page.href ?? page._path }}">...</a>
<a href="{{ section.href ?? section._path }}">...</a>

{# Pagination base URL #}
{% let base_url = base_url ?? section?.href ?? section?._path ?? '/blog/' %}
```

## Wrong

```html
{# ❌ Breaks on GitHub Pages project sites #}
<a href="{{ page._path ?? page.href }}">...</a>
<a href="{{ section._path ?? section.href }}">...</a>
```

---

## When to Use _path

Keep `_path` for **internal logic only** (not user-facing links):

- `rejectattr` / `is_current` comparisons (skip current page)
- Cache keys: `{% cache 'toc-' ~ (page?._path ?? 'unknown') %}`
- Deduplication: `rel_path in children_urls` when comparing same-page references

---

## Summary

- **Links**: `href ?? _path ?? path` (href first)
- **Internal logic**: `_path` is fine
